ly_7-25"><sup><i><b>z</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-The_Canadian_Family_7-26"><sup><i><b>aa</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-The_Canadian_Family_7-27"><sup><i><b>ab</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-The_Canadian_Family_7-28"><sup><i><b>ac</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-The_Canadian_Family_7-29"><sup><i><b>ad</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-The_Canadian_Family_7-30"><sup><i><b>ae</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-The_Canadian_Family_7-31"><sup><i><b>af</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-The_Canadian_Family_7-32"><sup><i><b>ag</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation book">Conway, John Fredrick (2003). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://books.google.com/books?id=-Spqsukv9aQC&pg=PA213&dq=double+burden+working+women&hl=en&ei=41G3TtOoCYTs0gHBvMz1Bg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDkQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&amp;q=double%20burden%20working%20women&amp;f=false"><i>The Canadian Family in Crisis</i></a>. James Lorimer &amp; Company. pp.&#160;213–232<span class="printonly">. <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://books.google.com/books?id=-Spqsukv9aQC&pg=PA213&dq=double+burden+working+women&hl=en&ei=41G3TtOoCYTs0gHBvMz1Bg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDkQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&amp;q=double%20burden%20working%20women&amp;f=false">http://books.google.com/books?id=-Spqsukv9aQC&amp;pg=PA213&amp;dq=double+burden+working+women&amp;hl=en&amp;ei=41G3TtOoCYTs0gHBvMz1Bg&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;ct=result&amp;resnum=3&amp;ved=0CDkQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&amp;q=double%20burden%20working%20women&amp;f=false</a></span>.</span></span></li>
